author: CNN
description:
Poland and NATO scrambled jets as Russia launched a large-scale air assault on Ukraine, targeting multiple locations including areas near Poland’s border. Just a day earlier, NATO intercepted three Russian fighter jets that briefly entered Estonian airspace, according to Estonia’s foreign ministry. CNN’s Boris Sanchez spoke with former NATO Supreme Allied Commander Adm. James Stavridis
for analysis on the escalating situation.   #CNN #News
title: Poland scrambles jets as Russia strikes Ukraine

author: CNN
description: Luigi Mangione’s lawyers urged a judge to bar federal prosecutors from seeking the death penalty in the killing of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson, arguing that authorities prejudiced his case by turning his arrest into a “Marvel movie” spectacle and by publicly declaring their desire to see him executed. CNN’s Leigh Waldman joins Boris Sanchez to discuss.   #CNN #News
title: Luigi Mangione’s lawyers want to remove death penalty from the case

author: CNN
description:
Staffers on “Jimmy Kimmel Live!” will remain on payroll for now as talks continue between Kimmel and Disney over the show’s future, following its abrupt indefinite suspension Wednesday.
The late-night program was pulled after Kimmel’s monologue about Charlie Kirk’s suspected killer sparked backlash.   #CNN #News
title: Kimmel show crew guaranteed pay for now as program’s fate hangs in balance

author: CNN
description:
For the first time, Farm Aid will stage its annual music and food festival in Minneapolis. Headliners include board members Willie Nelson, Neil Young, John Mellencamp, Dave Matthews with Tim Reynolds, and Margo Price, joined by Wynonna Judd and Kenny Chesney, organizers announced.
The all-day event will highlight local and organic foods while raising money to support Farm Aid’s year-round work with family farmers.   #CNN #News
title: Farm Aid marks 40 years with Nelson, Young and Mellencamp headlining Minneapolis show

author: CNN
description: Rep. Don Bacon (R-NE) joins CNN’s Manu Raju for a sit-down interview ahead of his retirement next year. Bacon represents one of House Republicans’ toughest battleground districts and has been one of the few Republicans willing to challenge Trump on key decisions in his second term. For more of the interview, watch “Inside Politics Sunday with Manu Raju” on Sunday at 8a and 11a ET on CNN. #CNN #News
title: GOP lawmaker skirts around question on Trump’s moral character

author: CNN
description: Thousands of people will gather to honor the life of assassinated conservative activist Charlie Kirk at a memorial service expected to underscore his indelible influence on American politics, with President Trump and other top officials set to speak. The high-profile event is drawing comparisons to a state funeral for the US conservative movement. It comes amid heightened security after an armed man posing as a police officer was arrested near the venue after he was “observed exhibiting suspicious behavior,” the Secret Service said. The Secret Service is leading the operation as Glendale police brace for crowds topping 100,000. CNN’s Betsy Klein reports.    #CNN #News
title: Inside Charlie Kirk’s memorial service: What to expect

author: CNN
description: Scientists have confirmed a rare great white shark nursery off the coast of the Hamptons, New York, where they are tagging juveniles to track their movements for conservation. Sightings of the predators have risen along the Northeast. CNN’s Leigh Waldman reports. #CNN #News
title: Great White Shark activity increasing in the Northeast

title: Kimmel drama is latest hit to free speech under Trump

description:
In the aftermath of Charlie Kirk's assassination, conspiracy theories across the political spectrum are spreading rapidly online. CNN's Marshall Cohen reports.

#CNN #News #CharlieKirk #Conspiracy #Politics
title: Charlie Kirk conspiracies spread online

author: CNN
description:
President Trump promised to lower grocery bills. But economists and companies say that his administration's policies are hiking grocery costs.

Grocery prices last month rose at their fastest pace in three years, stoked by Trump’s tariffs, a crackdown on immigration, and extreme weather hurting food production. Prices jumped 0.6% in August from the month prior, according to the latest reading from the Bureau of Labor Statistics, and they are up 2.7% from a year ago. Food prices are deeply personal to consumers, and weekly grocery bills shape their overall perceptions of the economy. More than half of Americans count grocery costs as a major stress in their lives.

The Federal Reserve on Wednesday lowered interest rates for the first time since December to support America’s faltering labor market. The Fed cut its benchmark lending rate by a quarter point to a new range of 4% to 4.25%. It’s the first rate cut of President Donald Trump’s second term, following a nine-month pause prompted
title: Trump's economic policies impacting grocery prices, mortgage rates

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump signed an executive order to implement a $100,000 application fee for H-1B visas in an effort to address what his administration claims is the overuse of the program. CNN’s Kristin Holmes explains what this means. #CNN #News
title: Trump imposes $100K fee on H-1B visas

author: CNN
description:
Protesters clashed with federal agents outside an ICE facility near Chicago Friday.

The facility in the village of Broadview has drawn small protests since its leaders got word in early September “a large-scale enforcement campaign will soon be underway” as part of the sweeping immigration agenda that helped secure a second term for President Donald Trump but most Americans oppose.

CNN's Danny Freeman speaks with Chicago alderman Byron Sigcho-Lopez. #CNN #News
title: Chicago activists push back against federal presence

author: CNN
description: The Trump administration abruptly suspended most Palestinian visas in August, derailing college plans for hundreds of Gazan students. CNN's Kylie Atwood spoke to one woman who fled Israel Gaza City offensive this week instead of setting up her American dorm room. #cnn #news
title: Trump policy derails Gazan students' plans

author: CNN
description: Sister Albertine Debacker, a 29-year-old who goes by ​⁠@soeur.albertine, is an influencer with a difference. She gives advice and shares details of her life as a Catholic nun to more than 500,000 followers. It’s part of a wider trend in France where the Catholic Church says it’s seeing an unexpected revival among Gen Z, fuelled in party by social media. CNN’s Joseph Ataman spoke to Sister Albertine at a youth festival in France to learn more about this fresh approach to faith.
title: Meet the influencers rebranding faith online

author: CNN
description: A telecommunication outage caused Federal Aviation Administration air traffic controllers in Dallas to lose radar and some communications, leading to flights being stopped at the area’s airports. After a virtual shut down of airports across the city, some flights were allowed to resume after 3:30 p.m. CT.
title: Flights finally resume after outages hit Dallas airports

description:
Backlash over a viral video that showed a student objecting to a children’s literature lesson about gender which led the president of Texas A&M University to step down from his position.
